  "prompt": "Is it a felony to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, in the United States and many other countries, money laundering is a felony.\n\nIn the U.S., money laundering is a federal crime under 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956 and 18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1957. Penalties can include significant prison time (up to 20 years per violation), substantial fines (up to $500,000 or double the amount of money laundered, whichever is greater), and forfeiture of assets involved in the crime.\n\nThe specifics of what constitutes money laundering and the associated penalties can vary slightly between jurisdictions, but it's generally treated as a serious crime.\n",
